 // Increment the static variable each time an object is created
 count++;
 }

 // Static method to get the current count
 public static int getCount() {
 return count;
 }
}
```
In this example, the `count` variable is a static variable that is used to keep track of the number of instances of the `Counter` class that have been created. The `getCount()` method is a static method that returns the current value of the `count` variable.

